show_title: The Great Tortoise Stampede: GM Farcaster ep299
text:
Why not add the ability to view each other‚Äôs holdings as easily as we can view each other‚Äôs casts?

Just add a tab in the same row as Casts, Replies, Collection, Likes on the profiles page.

I think I understand the valid argument for why not (i.e. intentional friction for the sake of privacy) but the recent addition of the ‚ÄúRecent trades‚Äù section I think implies the deprioritization of that specific type of privacy, if it can help lead to farcaster growth along with other wallet-focused changes.

The information is already public. What happens after it is made much easier for the masses to follow, I don‚Äôt know. People may value privacy more then and choose which wallets they connect to their socials more carefully, etc. But I don‚Äôt see a need for fc to delay the inevitable at this point.

Open to changing my mind. In navigating various pages and wallet things here, especially recent trades section, it just no longer feels like a material add-on as much as it feels like something that is actively missing. Seems very on theme with recent changes in prioritization.

text:
We‚Äôve reached peak media.

I think people will continue to shift towards more social-first platforms around their friends, family and communities.

People yearn for connection and humanity. Too much of technology subverts these two key things and I think people will continue to seek out human connection over content/media.

Hopefully will make everyone want to touch more grass, go out more, etc.
